Stage 1 - Virtual Environment Setup
-Installed VirtualBox on host system
-Created four virtual machines
 -Windows server 2022 (active directory domain controller)
 -Windows 10 (Domain-joined endpoint)
 -Kali Linux (Attack machine)
 -Splunk Server (Centralised logging and alerting) 
  -Updated. [sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get upgrade -y]
-Verified all systems boot successfully
-Created a custom NAT network
 -All machines share the 192.168.10.0/24 subnet

Stage 2 - Splunk Install and Configure
-Statically assigned IP to splunk server. [ip a] [sudo nano /etc/netplan/TAB FOR AUTO COMPLETE] [sudo netplan apply] 
 -Verified with ping 
-Installed guest additions and utils [sudo apt-get install virtualbox {TAB TO SHOW WHATS AVAILABLE}
-Created a share folder (Active_Directory_Project) [sudo reboot]
 -Contains Splunk Enterprise
-Added user to vboxsf group [sudo adduser arty vboxsf]
-Created new directory called 'share' [mkdir share] [ls] to check [ls -la] to list
 -Verified with ls command
-Mounted shared folder to share directory [sudo mount -t vboxsf -o uid=1000,gid=1000 Active_Directory_Project share/]
 -Downloaded Splunk Enterprise from share directory [cd share] to enter [ls -la] to list [sudo dpkg -i splunk{TAB TO AUTO FILL}] to install [cd /opt/splunk] go to splunk
  -[ls -la] show list [sudo -u splunk bash] to become splunk user [cd bin] enter bin [./splunk start] to install splunk [exit] [cd bin] [./splunk enable boot-start -user splunk] splunk to start up on boot

Stage 3 - Installing Sysmon and Splnuk Universal Forwarder on Splunk server and AD server
-Updated PC name
-Stactically assigned IP
-Verified Splunk is running via web brower
 -Error loading page
 -Used command in Splunk server to confirm status, was down [sudo /opt/splunk/bin/splunk status]
 -Used command to start Splunk [sudo /opt/splunk/bin/splunk start --accept-license]
 -Used command to confirm port 8000 was listening [sudo ss -tulnp | grep 8000] 
 -Enabled start on boot [sudo /opt/splunk/bin/splunk enable boot-start]
 -Confirmed Splunk status by attempting to access via GUI on target machine browser


